\meta{version}{"1.0"}

\meta{description}{Build and configure a resilient command-and-control infrastructure using BishopFox's Sliver C2 framework with redirectors, HTTPS listeners, and multi-operator support for authorized red team engagements.}

\subtree{
\title{Building C2 Infrastructure with Sliver Framework}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Sliver is an open-source, cross-platform adversary emulation framework developed by BishopFox, written in Go. It provides red teams with implant generation, multi-protocol C2 channels (mTLS, HTTP/S, DNS, WireGuard), multi-operator support, and extensive post-exploitation capabilities. Sliver supports beacon (asynchronous) and session (interactive) modes, making it suitable for both long-haul operations and interactive exploitation. A properly architected Sliver infrastructure uses redirectors, domain fronting, and HTTPS certificates to maintain operational resilience and avoid detection.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{When deploying or configuring building c2 infrastructure with sliver framework capabilities in your environment}
\li{When establishing security controls aligned to compliance requirements}
\li{When building or improving security architecture for this domain}
\li{When conducting security assessments that require this implementation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Familiarity with red teaming concepts and tools}
\li{Access to a test or lab environment for safe execution}
\li{Python 3.8+ with required dependencies installed}
\li{Appropriate authorization for any testing activities}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Objectives}
\ul{
\li{Deploy a Sliver team server on hardened cloud infrastructure}
\li{Configure HTTPS, mTLS, DNS, and WireGuard listeners}
\li{Generate implants (beacons and sessions) for target platforms}
\li{Set up NGINX or Apache redirectors between implants and the team server}
\li{Implement Cloudflare or CDN-based domain fronting for traffic obfuscation}
\li{Configure multi-operator access with certificate-based authentication}
\li{Establish operational security controls for C2 communications}
}
}

