\subtree{
\title{Phase 2: Listener Configuration}
\ol{
\li{Configure an HTTPS listener with a legitimate SSL certificate:}
\li{Configure a DNS listener for fallback C2:}
\li{Configure mTLS listener for high-security sessions:}
\li{Configure WireGuard listener for tunneled access:}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 3: Redirector Setup}
\ol{
\li{Deploy a separate VPS as a redirector (positioned between targets and team server)}
\li{Install and configure NGINX as a reverse proxy:}
}

\pre{\startverb
location / { proxy_pass https://<team-server-ip>:443; proxy_ssl_verify off; proxy_set_header Host $host; proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr; } }
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
3. Configure iptables rules on the team server to only accept connections from the redirector:
\stopverb}

\p{iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 443 -s <redirector-ip> -j ACCEPT iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 443 -j DROP}

\pre{\startverb
4. Optionally set up Cloudflare as a CDN layer in front of the redirector for domain fronting

\stopverb}
}

